        "client_msg_id": "20bd3c2e-f448-4284-84f8-aeb6de3f7a0a",
        "text": "Hi. I wonder if anyone knows how it is possible for packages on CRAN not have a depends value for R version? I am looking at the data with `tools::CRAN_package_db()` . Among other funny things I see is `R (&gt;= 7.3-0)` . :slightly_smiling_face:\nDoesn't CRAN enforce a check on a correct R version in the proper format for a package?",
        "team": "T01DW9DLB2A",
        "user_team": "T01DW9DLB2A",
        "source_team": "T01DW9DLB2A",
        "user_profile": {
            "avatar_hash": "gb7165c7adcc",
            "image_72": "https:\/\/secure.gravatar.com\/avatar\/b7165c7adcc4f536e01e72e671815259.jpg?s=72&d=https%3A%2F%2Fa.slack-edge.com%2Fdf10d%2Fimg%2Favatars%2Fava_0018-72.png",
            "first_name": "Novica",
            "real_name": "Novica",
            "display_name": "",
            "team": "T01DW9DLB2A",
            "name": "nnovica",
            "is_restricted": false,
            "is_ultra_restricted": false
        },
        "blocks": [
