                                    "italic": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": " R version, this makes sense as they make use facilities added a by a particular R version. Examples are when vignette processing changed etc.  But other CRAN packages do "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "not",
                                "style": {
                                    "italic": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": " specify a minimum R version, or a dependency on R at all as this is implicit.  E.g. my small package "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "zigg",
                                "style": {
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": " which wraps a simple set of (fast) C language random number generators does not declare a depends at all, see "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "link",
                                "url": "https:\/\/cran.r-project.org\/package=zigg"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": ".  I probably have other like that, as well as packages with a stale 'Depend:' on R in an old version. In fact I removed one of those this week.  So in short it may depend on what your package does, and if any of that is dependent on a particular minimal R version."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
