    {
        "user": "U04TQ0GBJ04",
        "type": "message",
        "ts": "1773777656.154589",
        "client_msg_id": "8598473f-ed7a-47a3-97c0-22c8d7e311f6",
        "text": "Then I think R went from 3.6.3 to 4.0.0 right? But then there are packages that depend on R 3.7.0 for example: <https:\/\/cran.r-project.org\/web\/packages\/etree\/>\n\nSo generally I am just wondering if or how CRAN checks\/enforces this.",
        "team": "T01DW9DLB2A",
        "user_team": "T01DW9DLB2A",
        "source_team": "T01DW9DLB2A",
        "user_profile": {
            "avatar_hash": "gb7165c7adcc",
            "image_72": "https:\/\/secure.gravatar.com\/avatar\/b7165c7adcc4f536e01e72e671815259.jpg?s=72&d=https%3A%2F%2Fa.slack-edge.com%2Fdf10d%2Fimg%2Favatars%2Fava_0018-72.png",
            "first_name": "Novica",
            "real_name": "Novica",
            "display_name": "",
            "team": "T01DW9DLB2A",
            "name": "nnovica",
            "is_restricted": false,
            "is_ultra_restricted": false
        },
        "attachments": [
            {
                "from_url": "https:\/\/cran.r-project.org\/web\/packages\/etree\/",
                "service_icon": "https:\/\/cran.r-project.org\/favicon.ico",
                "thumb_url": "https:\/\/CRAN.R-project.org\/CRANlogo.png",
                "thumb_width": 1000,
                "thumb_height": 1000,
                "id": 1,
                "original_url": "https:\/\/cran.r-project.org\/web\/packages\/etree\/",
                "fallback": "etree: Classification and Regression with Structured and Mixed-Type Data",
                "text": "Implementation of Energy Trees, a statistical model to perform classification and regression with structured and mixed-type data. The model has a similar structure to Conditional Trees, but brings in Energy Statistics to test independence between variables that are possibly structured and of different nature. Currently, the package covers functions and graphs as structured covariates. It builds upon 'partykit' to provide functionalities for fitting, printing, plotting, and predicting with Energy Trees. Energy Trees are described in Giubilei et al. (2022) &lt;<https:\/\/doi.org\/10.48550\/arXiv.2207.04430|doi:10.48550\/arXiv.2207.04430>&gt;.",
                "title": "etree: Classification and Regression with Structured and Mixed-Type Data",
                "title_link": "https:\/\/cran.r-project.org\/web\/packages\/etree\/",
                "service_name": "cran.r-project.org"
            }
        ],
        "blocks": [
            {
                "type": "rich_text",
                "block_id": "1Xg2r",
                "elements": [
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_section",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "Then I think R went from 3.6.3 to 4.0.0 right? But then there are packages that depend on R 3.7.0 for example: "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "link",
                                "url": "https:\/\/cran.r-project.org\/web\/packages\/etree\/"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "\n\nSo generally I am just wondering if or how CRAN checks\/enforces this."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "user": "U081Z9041A5",
        "type": "message",
        "ts": "1773782311.334679",
        "client_msg_id": "c8e3d1ea-3bc3-4317-b404-209640d68b00",
        "text": "&gt; if or how CRAN checks\/enforces this.\nIt's a boolean expression. So if a package says 'R (&gt;= 3.7.0)' then 3.6.3 does not pass and 4.0.0 does.  And no judgement on whether number corresponds to a release.",
        "team": "T01DW9DLB2A",
        "user_team": "T01DW9DLB2A",
        "source_team": "T01DW9DLB2A",
        "user_profile": {
            "avatar_hash": "g4e96ca7ae02",
            "image_72": "https:\/\/secure.gravatar.com\/avatar\/4e96ca7ae02c37e7d940d17997d780e5.jpg?s=72&d=https%3A%2F%2Fa.slack-edge.com%2Fdf10d%2Fimg%2Favatars%2Fava_0023-72.png",
            "first_name": "Dirk",
            "real_name": "Dirk Eddelbuettel",
            "display_name": "Dirk Eddelbuettel",
            "team": "T01DW9DLB2A",
            "name": "edd",
            "is_restricted": false,
            "is_ultra_restricted": false
        },
        "blocks": [
            {
                "type": "rich_text",
                "block_id": "6j8py",
                "elements": [
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_quote",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "if or how CRAN checks\/enforces this."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_section",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "It's a boolean expression. So if a package says 'R (>= 3.7.0)' then 3.6.3 does not pass and 4.0.0 does.  And no judgement on whether number corresponds to a release."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ],
